15:22.972 --> 15:26.224
Now it's weird. Mm-hmm.
Yep, the rain makes it weird.

15:26.226 --> 15:29.611
Mom, I'm not marrying
some future possibility

15:29.613 --> 15:31.229
of starting a family.

15:32.365 --> 15:33.498
I'm marrying a girl.

15:34.417 --> 15:37.169
Who means more to me than kids.

15:37.787 --> 15:39.421
Or my career.

15:39.423 --> 15:42.291
Or even the Lambor-cuzzi,
patent pending.

15:43.259 --> 15:45.510
So please...

15:46.346 --> 15:47.629
...be nice to her?

15:50.166 --> 15:52.668
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

15:52.670 --> 15:54.202
Get out there
and drag Clint's

15:54.204 --> 15:57.306
downward-facing ass back in here
so we can get going.

15:57.308 --> 15:59.891
Just let him do his thing.

16:01.928 --> 16:03.928
Do you know why
the Daphnes of the world

16:03.930 --> 16:05.530
always get to pick the music

16:05.532 --> 16:07.816
and the Marshalls pay
all the tolls?

16:07.818 --> 16:08.817
Because
the Marshalls

16:08.819 --> 16:10.619
are so concerned

16:10.621 --> 16:12.704
with letting everybody
do their thing,

16:12.706 --> 16:15.940
and the Daphnes
are taking care of Daphne.

16:15.942 --> 16:19.711
You can talk to me about solar
or wind or hydro-whatever,

16:19.713 --> 16:22.447
but the world is always gonna
push you around, Marshall.

16:22.449 --> 16:25.050
Until you learn
to go nuclear.

16:30.307 --> 16:31.947
What are you doing?

16:34.177 --> 16:35.844
Is this real?

16:35.846 --> 16:37.229
Are you doing this?

16:38.514 --> 16:39.848
We need some driving music.

16:39.850 --> 16:40.350
No!

16:44.971 --> 16:48.073
You threw a live grenade
into my marriage.

16:48.808 --> 16:51.660
You screwed up my whole world.

16:51.662 --> 16:54.746
So from now on...

16:54.748 --> 16:57.649
we listen to my music.

16:58.618 --> 17:02.153
♪ But I would walk 500 miles

17:02.155 --> 17:04.489
♪ And I would walk 500 more...

17:04.491 --> 17:06.258
I hate this song.

17:06.260 --> 17:07.709
Give it time.

17:09.829 --> 17:13.348
Zitch dog, beagle
in a Beetle.

17:13.349 --> 17:15.884
Don't let Loretta
get to you.

17:15.886 --> 17:19.186
Hey, when your mom gets here,
do you want to all go--

17:19.189 --> 17:22.858
I don't know--
avoid jellyfish?

17:22.859 --> 17:23.724
She's not coming.

17:23.727 --> 17:25.277
What?

17:25.279 --> 17:26.978
I finally got a hold of her.

17:26.980 --> 17:29.013
She, um, never got on the plane.

17:29.015 --> 17:30.565
She was too scared.

17:31.617 --> 17:33.151
She won't be
at her daughter's wedding.

17:40.294 --> 17:42.461
If that is the case...

17:42.463 --> 17:45.914
can we tell Barney
she's super fat?

17:45.916 --> 17:48.083
It would mean the world to me.

17:49.253 --> 17:50.802
Of course.

17:51.804 --> 17:53.221
Oh, here we go.

17:53.223 --> 17:54.589
Listen, Robin...
Loretta,

17:54.591 --> 17:57.041
not now. Robin just found out

17:57.043 --> 17:58.710
her mom's not coming
to the wedding.

18:02.648 --> 18:03.882
Oh.

18:03.884 --> 18:05.784
Well, uh, okay.

18:05.786 --> 18:07.002
Loretta...

18:07.004 --> 18:08.270
My name's Mom.

18:08.272 --> 18:10.388
Don't you ever call me
anything else.

18:10.390 --> 18:11.606
I'm Mom.

18:11.608 --> 18:13.892
Okay.

18:13.894 --> 18:15.093
Mom.

18:15.095 --> 18:17.329
I'm sorry.
Sometimes I get...

18:18.831 --> 18:20.499
...carried away.

18:23.252 --> 18:27.122
Your eggs are great, by the way.

18:27.124 --> 18:28.740
<i>Oh, mama,</i>

18:28.742 --> 18:30.509
that was some bad advice.

18:30.511 --> 18:31.760
Thanks, Lil.

18:32.428 --> 18:33.244
But you know what sucks?

18:33.246 --> 18:34.463
When I was
at the top

18:34.465 --> 18:35.630
of that lighthouse,

18:35.632 --> 18:37.432
despite everything else...

18:37.434 --> 18:40.385
Wow. It's like traveling
back in time.

18:40.387 --> 18:42.521
Just stop talking.

18:43.857 --> 18:45.307
<i>...it was breathtaking.</i>

18:45.309 --> 18:47.592
And I wasted it.

18:47.594 --> 18:49.611
I mean, how many places
have I ruined forever

18:49.613 --> 18:51.530
by being there
with the wrong girl?

18:51.532 --> 18:53.899
So come back
with the right girl.

18:53.901 --> 18:55.784
I don't know.

18:55.786 --> 18:58.069
I'm starting to think a person
gets a certain allotment

18:58.071 --> 19:00.772
of lighthouses per lifetime.

19:00.774 --> 19:03.041
And I've used all mine up.

19:03.043 --> 19:05.877
<i>And that, kids, is the kind</i>
<i>of stupid thing you say</i>

19:05.879 --> 19:08.112
<i>before you've met the person</i>
<i>who hits the reset button</i>

19:08.114 --> 19:10.665
<i>on the world,</i>
<i>who makes everything new again,</i>

19:10.667 --> 19:12.083
<i>who makes it seem ridiculous</i>

19:12.085 --> 19:14.219
<i>that you ever considered</i>
<i>settling,</i>

19:14.221 --> 19:16.671
<i>because not two years later...</i>

19:18.090 --> 19:20.291
Look at that.

19:23.846 --> 19:27.015
It's like traveling
back in time.

19:27.017 --> 19:30.018
That is exactly what I said.

19:30.020 --> 19:32.637
Why couldn't it have been you
here with me two years ago?

19:32.639 --> 19:34.906
That's probably
for the best.

19:34.908 --> 19:36.858
When you vomit, I vomit.

19:36.860 --> 19:38.309
You know that.

19:38.311 --> 19:42.697
Well, thanks for being
here with me now.

19:42.699 --> 19:44.482
Thanks for bringing me.

19:47.753 --> 19:49.821
Wow.

19:49.823 --> 19:53.658
It is just
bonkers beautiful here.

19:53.660 --> 19:57.495
I don't know how you could
improve on a day like this.

20:02.301 --> 20:04.436
Well, I'm gonna try.

20:10.977 --> 20:12.561
Whoa.

20:14.447 --> 20:15.564
Will you...

20:15.566 --> 20:16.481
Yes.

20:16.483 --> 20:18.450
You didn't even let me...

20:18.452 --> 20:19.401
Yes.

20:19.403 --> 20:20.685
Marry me?

20:20.687 --> 20:21.820
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

20:21.822 --> 20:24.739
